      "term": "Momentum Investing",
      "explanation_en": "Momentum investing means buying stocks that are already trending upward, based on the idea that assets showing strong recent performance tend to keep rising in the short term. Traders use signals like RSI (momentum strength), MACD (trend direction), and volume surges (institutional confirmation) to identify stocks with the best setup. The risk is that momentum can reverse sharply \u2014 which is why stop-losses are essential.",
